receips.desc:
1. Peel the fresh beetroot and grapefruit, then cut them into cubes.
2. You don't need to peel the apple, just remove the core and seeds. 
3. Wash the greens. If you have any fresh beet tops left, you can also add them to the smoothie.
4. In a blender bowl, combine beetroot, apple, grapefruit, greens, add almonds, and pour in a little water.
5. Blend until smooth. Pour the smoothie into a glass and garnish with greens.

1. 
Place the banana and apple cut into pieces into the blender bowl, add a slice of lemon. Grind until smooth.
2. 
You can adjust the consistency of the drink with water. Pour in the required amount and beat again.
3. 
Add chia seeds and leave for 3-5 minutes.
4. 
Pour the smoothie into a glass and enjoy the healthy drink.

1. 
Beat 2 chicken eggs into one bowl. Next, add cottage cheese (400 g), sprinkle the cottage cheese with sugar (4 tbsp), add vanilla sugar (10 g), and finally baking powder. Mix everything well with a whisk or spoon.
2. 
Set the resulting curd mass aside for now, then proceed with preparing the flour according to the recipe. It is necessary to sift it and set aside half for deboning the cheesecakes.
3. 
After this, add the curd dough to the flour and stir until smooth.
4. Form small round portions of cheesecakes. Grease a baking sheet with oil or cover with parchment, preheat the oven to 180 degrees. Then place the cakes on a baking sheet and place in the oven for 15-20 minutes.
5. 
Cool the dessert and serve with tea with sour cream or other sauce.

1. 
Soak 30 g and 15 g of gelatin in different containers in a small amount of cold boiled water. Roll out the dough into a thin layer.
2. Preheat the oven to 220°C. Cut a circle with a diameter of 30–32 cm from the dough and make frequent punctures on its surface with a fork. Grease a baking tray with oil. Place a circle of dough on a baking sheet and bake in the oven for 10 minutes until golden brown. The finished cake will shrink slightly in size.
3. 
Prepare custard. Stir milk, sugar and yolks in a bowl, place in a water bath and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Remove from heat, add 30 g of swollen gelatin and stir until completely dissolved. Cool.
4. 
Rub the cottage cheese through a sieve and beat the cream. Fold the cottage cheese and cream into the cooled custard. Dry the peaches with a napkin, cut into small pieces and add to the curd mass.
5. 
Place the frozen cherries in a saucepan, add sugar, and pour in enough water to barely cover the cherries. Bring to a boil, remove from heat and mix with remaining gelatin. Stir well and let cool.
6. Line a tall springform pan with cling film, place the baked crust on the bottom, and add curd and butter cream on it. Place in the refrigerator for 1–1.5 hours. The cream should harden. Then pour in the cherry mixture. Return to the refrigerator and leave until completely set. Before serving, remove the sides of the pan and remove the film.

1. Place the beef in a large saucepan, add 3 liters of cold water and bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low and skim thoroughly. Add bay leaf, whole onion and carrots, add salt and cook covered for 1 hour, avoiding boiling.
2. Cut the potatoes into cubes. Cut the second carrot and beet into strips. Cut the sweet pepper lengthwise, remove seeds and membranes, and cut the halves into strips. Cut the onion into small cubes. Chop the cabbage thinly. Grate the tomatoes. Chop the dill and parsley.
3. Heat vegetable oil in a deep frying pan and simmer the onion until transparent, 5 minutes. Add carrots, beets and bell peppers to the pan and fry over medium heat for 5 minutes. Add grated tomato, reduce heat and simmer covered for another 7 minutes. Stir several times.
4. Remove the meat from the pan and break it into small pieces. Strain the broth into a clean saucepan, remove the vegetables, they will not be needed. Bring the broth to a boil again and add the potatoes. Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
5. 
Add the vegetables from the skillet to the pan. After 5 minutes, add the prepared cabbage and meat to the borscht and cook for another 5 minutes. Leave the borscht to steep for 10 minutes. Pour into plates, sprinkle with herbs and serve with sour cream.

1. Cut the onion into small cubes.
2. Melt the butter in a saucepan and fry the chopped onion in it for 7-8 minutes until soft.
3. Peel the potatoes and cut them into very small cubes. The smaller the pieces, the faster the whole dish will cook.
4. 
Place the chopped potatoes in a saucepan with the fried onions.
5. Separate the cauliflower into florets and rinse under running water.
6. 
Place the cauliflower florets in the pan with the potatoes and onions, add enough hot water to cover the vegetables. Add also salt and ground black pepper to taste. Let the water boil again and cook the soup for 20-25 minutes.
7. 
Using a blender, puree the vegetables, gradually adding broth until the soup reaches the thickness you need.
8. Pour the cream into the soup, mix everything again and heat the soup over the fire for 2-3 minutes (do not boil!!)
9. Creamy cauliflower soup is ready. Pour the soup into serving bowls and serve with croutons or fresh bread.

articles.title: Lose weight without harm to health
articles.titleDesc: Every modern person is increasingly convinced that it is very important and necessary to lead a healthy lifestyle. The problem of excess weight is becoming more and more urgent.
articles.desc: Every modern person is increasingly convinced that it is very important and necessary to lead a healthy lifestyle. The problem of excess weight is becoming more and more urgent.To lose weight, you need mandatory physical activity, but your diet is also very important. This article will focus specifically on healthy eating.The rhythm of life has accelerated so much that many do not have time to prepare themselves a full meal and are forced to subsist on fast food and soda.To make weight loss easier and not cause a constant feeling of hunger and the risk of relapse, you need to replace your usual food recipes with healthy recipes.There are now a lot of healthy recipes for dishes; they can be easily found on the Internet on culinary sites and forums.

articles.title: Vitamins and their role in a healthy diet
articles.titleDesc: Food should provide us with the necessary amount of fats, proteins, carbohydrates, microelements, water and of course vitamins.
articles.desc: Food should provide us with the necessary amount of fats, proteins, carbohydrates, microelements, water and of course vitamins.Many vitamins are not produced by our body at all; some are synthesized in insufficient quantities, so we must receive them from the outside, that is, with food. Experts say that 90% of vitamins are replenished from food.Speaking about a healthy diet, you need to understand that vitamins must enter our body with fruits and vegetables, meat, fish, and dairy products. Those vitamins that we purchase at the pharmacy in the form of capsules and tablets are chemical analogues, produced artificially. It is better to buy them in exceptional cases and with a doctor's prescription.A healthy diet and a balanced supply of vitamins will protect our body from drowsiness, permanent fatigue, nervousness, depression and other “modern scourges”.The result of a healthy diet (vitamin) is a beautiful appearance, youth and excellent mood.

articles.title: Healing properties of mushrooms
articles.titleDesc: Mushrooms are a popular tool in folk medicine. Scientific research into their healing qualities began in the 50s of the 20th century.
articles.desc: Mushrooms are a popular tool in folk medicine. Scientific research into their healing qualities began in the 50s of the 20th century.The healing properties of leaf polypore tincture are used in the treatment of pulmonary diseases, in particular tuberculosis. You can also stop its development with chanterelle extract.In addition, this mushroom is used to treat sore throats, abscesses, boils, or is used in powder form as an anthelmintic, which must be taken a teaspoon per day for more than a week..

articles.title: Beneficial properties of green tea
articles.titleDesc: Tea is an evergreen shrub that is native to Asia. To make any type of tea, leaves of the same tea bush are used. The resulting tea depends on the degree of fermentation. The healthiest variety is green tea, which has not been processed.
articles.desc: Tea is an evergreen shrub that is native to Asia. To make any type of tea, leaves of the same tea bush are used. The resulting tea depends on the degree of fermentation. The healthiest variety is green tea, which has not been processed.Mate tea, which is native to South America, is very fashionable now.Mate is rich in vitamins B, E and C. Thanks to the choline it contains, it reduces cholesterol levels. Mate leaves are used to produce extracts used in cosmetology, because mate moisturizes, disinfects, reduces inflammation, relieves pain, tones and regenerates.Tea extracts are used in the production of cosmetics. They give creams sun protection properties, anti-cellulite and anti-aging effects.In medicine, tea is used externally as an infusion. It relieves swelling and inflammation, fights bacteria, and stimulates. Blepharitis and burns are treated with it.
